betterquesting.name: Tables
betterquesting.desc: To begin with you have to craft following tables

betterquesting.name: Chests
betterquesting.desc: If you don't want to search everytime you need a pattern or part: craft a chest.

betterquesting.name: Patterns and Parts
betterquesting.desc: To craft some tools we will need some parts. Therefor we will need some patterns.

betterquesting.name: Drying
betterquesting.desc: You can use the drying rack for all sorts of things.

betterquesting.name: Hammer
betterquesting.desc:
To start with Immersive Engineering you need to craft a hammer.
If you are building structures in Immersive Engineering you always have to click the structure at a specific location to form the complete structure.

betterquesting.name: Coke Oven
betterquesting.desc: The Coke Oven does not only produce coal coke it also produces cresoete oil what you'll need later on.

betterquesting.name: Wood
betterquesting.desc: Get some wood

betterquesting.name: Stone
betterquesting.desc: Craft a wooden pickaxe and get some cobblestone.

betterquesting.name: Farmer
betterquesting.desc:
The farmer will plant and harvest in a 9x9 area infront of it.

The left side of the GUI is for seeds to plant and the right side for harvested goods.

It needs power.

betterquesting.name: Getting resources
betterquesting.desc: Walk through the world to find some resources.

betterquesting.name: Mobs
betterquesting.desc: Kill some mobs.

betterquesting.name: Oven
betterquesting.desc: Craft a furnace.

betterquesting.name: Treated Wood
betterquesting.desc: What can you do with your creosite oil...

betterquesting.name: Waterwheel
betterquesting.desc: Your first Powergeneration

betterquesting.name: windmill
betterquesting.desc: Use wind to power your machines.

betterquesting.name: wooden post
betterquesting.desc: for power lines or windmills a wooden post is a nice ground structure.

betterquesting.name: lv connector
betterquesting.desc: low voltage energy transfer.

betterquesting.name: lv capacitor
betterquesting.desc: low voltage battery

betterquesting.name: iron
betterquesting.desc: Mining can be helpful.

betterquesting.name: silver
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: tin
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: copper
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: gold
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: lead
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Getting seeds
betterquesting.desc: Punch grass to get seeds.

betterquesting.name: sails
betterquesting.desc: to get more power off a windmill you have put on sails by rightclicking the windmill.

betterquesting.name: gems
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Seared Bricks
betterquesting.desc: Grout is used to make a smeltery.

betterquesting.name: Melter
betterquesting.desc: small version of smeltery. Just place a bucket of lava into the tank and the melter ontop of the tank and you have your working smeltery.

betterquesting.name: Casts
betterquesting.desc: With casts you can make your metal solid.

betterquesting.name: Drill
betterquesting.desc: A powered drill is like a pickaxe.

betterquesting.name: Blast Furnace
betterquesting.desc: It needs coal coke and iron and produces steel.

betterquesting.name: Steel
betterquesting.desc:
The good old steel.

Just throw some iron and coal coke into the blast furnace and make you a cup of coffee....

betterquesting.name: Nether
betterquesting.desc: Get some obsidian, and a flint and steel and get some nether rack.

betterquesting.name: Killing in nether
betterquesting.desc: Killing in nether is quite some fun.

betterquesting.name: Enori
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing iron infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Atomic Reconstructor
betterquesting.desc: It is used to turn mineraft items into new ones by throwing them infront of the atomic reconstructor and powering it with RF.

betterquesting.name: Palis
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing Lapislazuli infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Restonia
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing Redstone infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Void
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing coal infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Diamatine
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing diamond infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Emeradic
betterquesting.desc: It is obtained by throwing emerald infront of the Atomic Reconstructor.

betterquesting.name: Light Engineering
betterquesting.desc:
Used in some machines.
See the manual to get more information about which machine needs what.

betterquesting.name: Redstone Engineering
betterquesting.desc:
Used in some machines.
See the manual to get more information about which machine needs what.

betterquesting.name: Heavy Engineering
betterquesting.desc:
Used in some machines.
See the manual to get more information about which machine needs what.

betterquesting.name: Drill Core
betterquesting.desc: Could drilling be better than picking?

betterquesting.name: Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.desc:
This is the item transport system of immersive engineering.

Items won't despawn on here.

betterquesting.name: Kill mobs
betterquesting.desc: For resources.

betterquesting.name: Basic Coil
betterquesting.desc: An often used crafting material.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Coil
betterquesting.desc: Good that there is a use for gold now ;)

betterquesting.name: Vertical Digger
betterquesting.desc:
The Vertical Digger has two modes: "Mining Everything" and "Only Mining Ores".

It will dig straight down until it hits Bedrock.

Per default, the Vertical Digger has a radius of 2 blocks, meaning it mines in a 5x5 area.

Placing a Phantom Booster on top of it will double the radius.
Up to 3 Phantom Boosters can be stacked above the digger, allowing a maximum radius of 16 (or 33x33).

betterquesting.name: Energy Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc:
Can transmit power to another energy laser.

You have to connect them with the laser wrench.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Energy Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc: Like the basic one but can send/receive more energy.

betterquesting.name: Extreme Energy Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc: Like the advanced one but can send/receive more energy.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Item Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc: Like the basic one but can send/receive faster.

betterquesting.name: Coal Generator
betterquesting.desc:
You need power?

Here you have it.

betterquesting.name: Oil Generator
betterquesting.desc: Burning oil = good power

betterquesting.name: Canola Press
betterquesting.desc:
You need oil to generate power?

Meet the Canola Press!

betterquesting.name: Fermenting Barrel
betterquesting.desc: You want more efficient oil?

betterquesting.name: Automatic Feeder
betterquesting.desc: Place it in your stable and feed it with wheat or whatever your pet may like and it will feed it to them.

betterquesting.name: Cart Assembler
betterquesting.desc: To assemble your carts you need this block and lots of coal.

betterquesting.name: Small Storage Crate
betterquesting.desc: a bigger chest

betterquesting.name: Medium Storage Crate
betterquesting.desc: a bigerer chest

betterquesting.name: Large Storage Crate
betterquesting.desc: a bigerererererererer chest

betterquesting.name: Fishing Net
betterquesting.desc:
To use the fishing net you just place it above a water source.

To automate it just put a chest ontop.

betterquesting.name: Crusher
betterquesting.desc: it can crush nearly everything into bits and pieces.

betterquesting.name: Double Crusher
betterquesting.desc: Nice, a second slot.

betterquesting.name: Powered Furnace
betterquesting.desc: WOW. Two slots to bake something and you just need power.

betterquesting.name: Solar Panel
betterquesting.desc: If you don't like emitting so much CO2 from your coal and oil you can switch to a solar panel.

betterquesting.name: Heat Collector
betterquesting.desc: Generates power if there is a lava source nearby.

betterquesting.name: Item Repairer
betterquesting.desc: It has to be magic to repair everything with electricity.

betterquesting.name: Greenhouse Glass
betterquesting.desc: If a plant sees the sky through this block it is likely to grow faster.

betterquesting.name: Auto-Breaker
betterquesting.desc: Helps you breaking blocks.

betterquesting.name: Auto-Placer
betterquesting.desc: Helps you placing blocks

betterquesting.name: Automatic Precision Dropper
betterquesting.desc: Helps you dropping items to the ground.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Placer
betterquesting.desc: Helps you placing fluids.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Collector
betterquesting.desc: Helps you collecting fluids.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc: Like the energy laser but for fluids.

betterquesting.name: Item Laser Relay
betterquesting.desc: Like the energy laser but for items.

betterquesting.name: Crystallized Canola Seeds
betterquesting.desc: To get even better oil, place the fermented oil on the ground and throw in a crystallized canola seed to get crystallized canola.

betterquesting.name: Empowered Canola Seeds
betterquesting.desc: The best oil you can get is obtained by throwing en empowered canola seed into crystallized oil.

betterquesting.name: mv connector
betterquesting.desc: Mid voltage energy transfer.

betterquesting.name: hv connector
betterquesting.desc: High voltage energy transfer

betterquesting.name: mv capacitor
betterquesting.desc: Mid voltage battery

betterquesting.name: hv capacitor
betterquesting.desc: High voltage battery

betterquesting.name: Electrum
betterquesting.desc:
Conductivity of precious metals are higher than copper or iron.
Combining them could be even more powerful.

betterquesting.name: Aluminum
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Nickel
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Ardite
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Cobalt
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Zinc
betterquesting.desc: Mining can help.

betterquesting.name: Constantan
betterquesting.desc: Its high thermal conductivity makes it really good for thermal power generation.

betterquesting.name: Alumite
betterquesting.desc: Aluminum itself is not very hard, so combining it could make it a good tool component.

betterquesting.name: Invar
betterquesting.desc: It was reborn for a technical reason.

betterquesting.name: Knightslime
betterquesting.desc: This just looks cool... even at knighttime

betterquesting.name: Pigiron
betterquesting.desc: Don't hit it or it will hit you ;)

betterquesting.name: Cart Assembler
betterquesting.desc: To assemble your carts you need this block and lots of coal.

betterquesting.name: Manyullyn
betterquesting.desc: As if Ardite and Cobalt wasn't already enough...

betterquesting.name: Bronze
betterquesting.desc: Copper is good for electricity but for weapons and tools we need something more durable.

betterquesting.name: Aluminum Brass
betterquesting.desc: If you don't like wasting gold for casts... well here is your substitute.

betterquesting.name: Brass
betterquesting.desc: If you don't like wasting gold for casts... well here is your substitute.

betterquesting.name: Reinforced Blast Furnace
betterquesting.desc: Improving your Blast Furnace could be useful.

betterquesting.name: Empowerer
betterquesting.desc:
This is the second tier of actually additions.

You'll need 1 Empowerer and 4 Display stands

You'll have to place them in a + pattern with the Empowerer in the middle and on each side 3 blocks away 1 Display stand.

Now you have to power the 4 Display stands and follow the crafting recepies in JEI.

betterquesting.name: Wood Casing
betterquesting.desc: Wood you believe that?

betterquesting.name: Blast Furnace Preheater
betterquesting.desc:
If you want to speed up your steel production, you'll need two of these, one on each side of the blast furnace.

It could be a good idea to build another coke oven though because this uses the coke coal quite faster than usual.

betterquesting.name: External Heater
betterquesting.desc: If you are tired of throwing coal into your furnaces... you can power them with electricity by placing this block near to your furnace

betterquesting.name: Engineer's Workbench
betterquesting.desc: You need blueprints to craft on this workbench.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Router
betterquesting.desc: Useful to organize your liquids.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Pipe
betterquesting.desc: Useful for transporting fluids.

betterquesting.name: Generator Block
betterquesting.desc: See the manual for the diesel generator.

betterquesting.name: Radiator Block
betterquesting.desc: See the manual for the diesel generator.

betterquesting.name: Transformer
betterquesting.desc: To connect lv with mv you need a transformer.

betterquesting.name: Iron Casing
betterquesting.desc: Try sawing this by hand.

betterquesting.name: Ender Casing
betterquesting.desc: Even if you think you can, you cannot store ender pearls in here.

betterquesting.name: Empowered Restonia
betterquesting.desc: Mhhh.... Looks shiny :)

betterquesting.name: Empowered Palis
betterquesting.desc: Mhhh.... Looks shiny :)

betterquesting.name: Empowered Enori
betterquesting.desc: Mhhh.... Looks shiny :)

betterquesting.name: Empowered Void
betterquesting.desc: Mhhh.... Looks shiny :)

betterquesting.name: Empowered Emeradic
betterquesting.desc: Looks like you are playing with a few mods now :D

betterquesting.name: Empowered Diamatine
betterquesting.desc: Looks like you loved to play embers ;)

betterquesting.name: Smart Output
betterquesting.desc: A fast way to make parts and ingots.

betterquesting.name: Smeltery
betterquesting.desc:
A fast way to make parts and ingots.
And a way to create alloys.

betterquesting.name: HV Transformer
betterquesting.desc: transforms mid to high voltage and vice versa

betterquesting.name: Blue Slime Sapling
betterquesting.desc: Look for flying islands.

betterquesting.name: Purple Slime Sapling
betterquesting.desc: Look for flying islands.

betterquesting.name: Magma Slime Sapling
betterquesting.desc: Look for islands in the nether.

betterquesting.name: Kinetic Dynamo
betterquesting.desc: The Block that generates the power.

betterquesting.name: Breaker Switch
betterquesting.desc: A fancy lever

betterquesting.name: Redstone Breaker
betterquesting.desc: a switch for power.

betterquesting.name: Engineer's Voltmeter
betterquesting.desc: It will show you how much Energy is in a capacitor and it will show you how much energy is lost between two connectors.

betterquesting.name: Current Transformer
betterquesting.desc: It shows you how much Energy is transmitting.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Pump
betterquesting.desc:
Can pump liquids.
Needs a redstone signal.
Click with the hammer on a side to get in/outputs.

betterquesting.name: Thermoelectric Generator
betterquesting.desc: A way to generate power by using two liquids with different temperatures.

betterquesting.name: Core Sample Drill
betterquesting.desc: To see which materials you can get when you build an excavator, you can drill a sample with this machine.

betterquesting.name: Tesla Coil
betterquesting.desc: Another way to generate power is using lightnings. Connect this coil to a grid of iron bars.

betterquesting.name: Garden Cloche
betterquesting.desc:
A simple way to automate harvesting plants.
You need the grow medium (like dirt), the seed, power on the top and water from the side.
If you want, you can throw in some bone meal to let them grow faster.

betterquesting.name: Vacuum Tube
betterquesting.desc: Who doesn't like a vacuum?

betterquesting.name: Dropping Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.desc:
If it can it puts items into an inventory beneath the belt.

If there is no inventory it will just let it drop down.

betterquesting.name: Splitting Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.desc: Just try it out.

betterquesting.name: Vertical Conveyor Belt
betterquesting.desc:
To get to upper levels use this.

To get to lower levels... just let it drop down.

betterquesting.name: Atmospheric Gauge
betterquesting.desc: You can use this to search for the best position of your ember bore.

betterquesting.name: Caminite Blend
betterquesting.desc: What a strange name.... Caminite

betterquesting.name: Mechanical Core
betterquesting.desc: For many big structures in Embers you need a mechanical core at the bottom to get in and outputs.

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Hammer
betterquesting.desc:
To get started with embers, you need this hammer.

It is used to craft plates.

However you can also use the hammer from immersive engineering.

betterquesting.name: Ember Bore
betterquesting.desc:
For getting ember(energy) you need ember crystals.

To get them you have to place the ember bore on bedrock and pipe coal into it.
Then you can extract ember crystals and ember shards.

betterquesting.name: Universal Bin
betterquesting.desc: For item storage there are these bins.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Vessel
betterquesting.desc: For fluid storage you can use this.

betterquesting.name: Item Pipe
betterquesting.desc: For item transportation you need the pipes and an item extractor.

betterquesting.name: Item Extractor
betterquesting.desc: The item extractor has to be placed on the inventory you want to draw items out of and has to be powered with a redstone signal.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Pipe
betterquesting.desc: For fluid transportation you need the pipes and a fluid extractor.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Extractor
betterquesting.desc: The fluid extractor has to be placed on the tank you want to draw liquids out of and has to be powered with a redstone signal.

betterquesting.name: Copper Cell
betterquesting.desc: A small ember(energy) battery.

betterquesting.name: Ember Emitter/Receptor
betterquesting.desc:
To transfer ember(energy) you have to use the Ember Emitter and Receptor.

The Emitter needs a redstone signal.

To connect them grab your Tinker's Hammer and Shift+Rightclick on the Receptor and then normal Rightclick on the Emitter.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Dial
betterquesting.desc: Put this on a tank and you see how much is in there.

betterquesting.name: Ember Dial
betterquesting.desc: Put this on any machine and you see how much ember(energy) is in there.

betterquesting.name: Reservoir
betterquesting.desc:
This is a kind of modular tank for fluids.

You need Caminite Rings ontop and with each ring you get more storage.

betterquesting.name: Caminite Ring
betterquesting.desc: Use it to upgrade your reservoir.

betterquesting.name: Melter
betterquesting.desc: It can melt stuff.

betterquesting.name: Machine Accessor
betterquesting.desc: if the mechanical core does not give you enough in and outputs you can put a machine accessor on each side to get 2 more in and outputs.

betterquesting.name: Ember Activator
betterquesting.desc: It is used to make ember(energy) out of ember crystals.

betterquesting.name: Hearth Coil
betterquesting.desc:
This is a big BBQ in Minecraft.

It works like a furnace but needs ember(energy) and you have to throw everything onto it.

betterquesting.name: Item Dropper
betterquesting.desc: it can drop items on the ground or on machines.

betterquesting.name: Stamper
betterquesting.desc: Let one air block between the stamper base (at the bottom) at the stamper (at the top).

betterquesting.name: Mixer Centrifuge
betterquesting.desc:
In here you can make Dawnstone.

Fill the mixer centrifuge from different sides at the upper half and extract the result at the lower half.

betterquesting.name: Ember Relay
betterquesting.desc: With this you can bridge your beam between the Emitter and Receptor.

betterquesting.name: Beam Splitter
betterquesting.desc: Can split the ember(energy) beam into up to 3 beams.

betterquesting.name: Crystal Cell
betterquesting.desc:
A big ember(energy) Battery.

To increase the capacity you have to pipe in ember crystals or shards.

betterquesting.name: Cinder Plinth
betterquesting.desc: You can throw anything in here and it will burn it to ash.

betterquesting.name: Exchange Tablet
betterquesting.desc: This is the heart of your Rituals.

betterquesting.name: Alchemy Pedestal
betterquesting.desc:
You will need 6 Alchemy Pedestals for your rituals.

Place your aspecti onto the pedestals.

For each ritual you have to put different amount of coal into different pedestals.

betterquesting.name: Beam Cannon
betterquesting.desc:
If your ritual is ready to start, then you have to shoot with the beam cannon onto the exchange tablet.

But be careful this cannon is very strong.

betterquesting.name: Caminite Brick
betterquesting.desc: What will happen if you put caminite blend in a furnace?

betterquesting.name: Caminite Plate
betterquesting.desc: A more useful state of caminite than the blend.

betterquesting.name: Dawnstone
betterquesting.desc: That looks impressive.

betterquesting.name: Stamps
betterquesting.desc: Used in the stamper to stamp different items.

betterquesting.name: Aspecti
betterquesting.desc:
To make an aspectus you need the molten metal in the stamper.

Then put in a ember crystal and there we go....

betterquesting.name: Ash
betterquesting.desc: Don't eat it.

betterquesting.name: Ashen Fabric
betterquesting.desc: who wants to wear something like this.

betterquesting.name: Nether Star
betterquesting.desc:
Wither bosses could be helpful to get these miqhty nether stars.

For those who don't know how to spawn one, you'll need soul sand and three witherskeletton skulls.
Then you place the soul sand in a T pattern and place the skulls on top of the soul sand.

betterquesting.name: Tinkers Construct
betterquesting.desc: The Journey starts...

betterquesting.name: Immersive Engineering
betterquesting.desc: Your first Power Generation and only source for steel.

betterquesting.name: Minecraft
betterquesting.desc: The basic minecraft quests.

betterquesting.name: Utilities
betterquesting.desc: Dark Utilities, Ender Storage, Exchangers, YABBA
